<T>__{cut to:}
<C>__{moxica}
<P>__{(to the clerk)}
<D>__{i can't? i can't?}
<A>__{with a single swift action, moxica draws his sword and cuts off the indian's hands. all hell breaks loose. the indians flee, disappearing into the jungle. giacomo arrives at this moment. he stares at the dismembered hands in horror.}
<L>__{interior governor's mansion evening}
<A>__{a tribunal. sitting behind a table with his brothers, and flanked by his council, columbus presides. moxica stands before them.}
<C>__{columbus}
<D>__{in one act of brutality, you have created chaos. tribes who were fighting each other are now joining forces against us! all that because of your criminal savagery!}
<C>__{moxica}
<P>__{(casually)}
<D>__{savagery is what monkeys understand.}
<C>__{columbus}
<D>__{you'll be held in detention, deprived of your privileges and possessions. until you are returned to spain where you will be judged. have you anything to say?}
<C>__{moxica}
<P>__{(with exquisite insolence)}
<D>__{you will regret this.}
<A>__{he strolls to the guards at the back of the room.}
